{"id": 2541, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2018", "session": "18N", "subtopic": "4-5-standing-waves", "title": "18N.1.SL.TZ0.17", "topic_id": "4", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Two strings of lengths <em>L</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>L</em><sub>2</sub> are fixed at both ends. The wavespeed is the same for both strings. They both vibrate at the same frequency. <em>L</em><sub>1</sub> vibrates at its first harmonic. <em>L</em><sub>2</sub> vibrates at its third harmonic.</p>\n<p>What is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{{L_1}}}{{{L_2}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msub>\n<mi>L</mi>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</msub>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msub>\n<mi>L</mi>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</msub>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A.   <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{3}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>3</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.   1</p>\n<p>C.   2</p>\n<p>D.   3</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}